---
import DocsLayout from '@/layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
---
<DocsLayout
  title="shuttle deploy"
  description="Full reference for the deploy command: flags, pipeline steps, and exit codes."
  section="commands"
>
  <p>
    <code>shuttle deploy</code> builds your Docker image, distributes it to every configured
    host in parallel, runs health checks, and atomically switches the proxy upstream. It is the
    primary command you run (or automate in CI) on every release.
  </p>

  <h2>Usage</h2>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle deploy [flags]
</code></pre>

  <h2>Flags</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Flag</th>
        <th>Default</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--skip-build</code></td>
        <td><code>false</code></td>
        <td>Skip local Docker build and image transfer. The server pulls the image from the configured registry. Use in CI after a separate build step.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--dry-run</code></td>
        <td><code>false</code></td>
        <td>Print what would be deployed (strategy, services, hooks) without making any SSH connections or changes.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--verbose</code></td>
        <td><code>false</code></td>
        <td>Print debug output including SSH commands and Docker output.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--config &lt;path&gt;</code></td>
        <td>auto-discover</td>
        <td>Explicit path to <code>shuttle.yml</code>.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--env &lt;name&gt;</code></td>
        <td><code>SHUTTLE_ENV</code></td>
        <td>Load <code>shuttle.&lt;name&gt;.yml</code> overlay on top of the base config.</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Full deploy pipeline</h2>
  <p>
    Here is what happens when you run <code>shuttle deploy</code>:
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <strong>Load and validate config</strong> — reads <code>shuttle.yml</code> (plus any env overlay),
      validates it with Zod, and normalizes <code>server:</code> shorthand to <code>servers:</code>.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Flatten server groups</strong> — collects all hosts from all server groups into a single
      list with their group name and SSH user.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Parallel host dispatch</strong> — dispatches all hosts in parallel using a semaphore
      with <code>deploy.concurrency</code> (default: 5). Each host runs the following pipeline
      independently:
      <ol>
        <li>Open SSH connection</li>
        <li>Acquire deploy lock (<code>mkdir /opt/shuttle/&lt;app&gt;/.deploy.lock</code>)</li>
        <li>Write in-flight state to <code>deploying.json</code></li>
        <li>Ensure accessories are running (<code>docker run</code> for each accessory)</li>
        <li>Run <code>pre_deploy</code> hooks via SSH (failure aborts deploy)</li>
        <li>For each service: execute the configured deploy strategy (blue-green / rolling / swarm)</li>
        <li>Run <code>post_deploy</code> hooks via SSH (failure is warning only)</li>
        <li>Clear in-flight state</li>
        <li>Release deploy lock</li>
        <li>Close SSH connection</li>
      </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Collect results</strong> — after all parallel tasks complete, errors are aggregated.
      If any host failed, the command exits with code 1 and prints a summary of failures.
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Dry run</h2>
  <p>
    Use <code>--dry-run</code> to preview what a deploy would do without making any changes:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle deploy --dry-run
# [dry-run] Host 203.0.113.10
# [dry-run] Strategy: blue-green
# [dry-run] Services: web
# [dry-run] pre_deploy hooks: php artisan migrate --force
</code></pre>
  <p>
    Dry run mode iterates over all hosts sequentially (not in parallel) and prints the config
    that would be applied to each one.
  </p>

  <h2>Skip build (CI mode)</h2>
  <p>
    In CI pipelines where a separate job builds and pushes the image, use <code>--skip-build</code>:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash"># CI build job pushes: ghcr.io/org/my-app:abc1234
# CI deploy job:
shuttle deploy --skip-build
</code></pre>
  <p>
    The server will <code>docker pull</code> the image from the registry configured in
    <code>shuttle.yml</code>.
  </p>

  <h2>Exit codes</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Code</th>
        <th>Meaning</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>0</code></td>
        <td>All hosts deployed successfully</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>1</code></td>
        <td>One or more hosts failed; error details printed to stderr</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</DocsLayout>
